<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-10T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-10T17:00:00-05:00" n="1196" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1196">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 367.11/171</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MH1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Morgenthau</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <dateline>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="italic">Constantinople</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-11T00:00:00+02:00">
                                <hi rend="italic">August 11, 1914, 12 midnight</hi>.</date>
                            <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received August 16, 8:20 p.m.</hi>] </dateline>
                        <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                        <p>Consul <persName corresp="#p_JJB1">Jackson</persName> telegraphs to-day
                            that owing to critical situation and financial crisis fears exist for
                            public safety and for the preservation of American lives and interests
                            and also as an act of humanity American ships should be sent to Syrian
                            ports.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_MH1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Morgenthau</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>